[SN]TITLE[SN]
Adam Buxton: Tranmere Rovers sign former Portsmouth defender

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Tranmere Rovers have signed defender Adam Buxton on a free transfer on a deal until the end of the season after his departure from Portsmouth.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The 24-year-old, who can play across the defence, mutually agreed to cancel his contract at the League Two club.
The former Wigan trainee moved to Pompey from Accrington at the start of the season and featured four times.
"He is a strong defender who will add to our options at this important stage of the season," said boss Micky Mellon.
